final List<Map<String, String>> devotions2026Enhanced = [
  // JANUARY 2026 - Enhanced with Stories, Thoughts, Actions, Confessions
  
  {'date': '2026-01-01', 'title': 'New Year, New Life in Christ', 'scripture': '2 Corinthians 5:17', 'body': 'Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation; old things have passed away; behold, all things have become new.\n\nAs we begin 2026, remember that every day with Jesus is a fresh start. His love renews us daily and gives us hope for transformation.', 'story': 'Sarah had struggled with the same destructive habits for years. Every January, she\'d resolve to change, only to fall back into the same patterns by February. But this year was different. She didn\'t rely on willpower alone. She invited Jesus into her struggle, asking Him to transform her from the inside out. Week by week, with His help, the old patterns lost their grip. Three months in, she realized she hadn\'t even thought about her old habits—Jesus had made her new.', 'thoughts': 'Today, reject the lie that you\'re stuck in your old ways. Christ\'s resurrection power is available to you right now. What area of your life needs to be made new in 2026?', 'action': 'Write down one habit or mindset you want Christ to transform this year. Place it somewhere visible as a reminder of your commitment.', 'confession': 'Lord, I confess that I cannot change myself. I need Your transforming power. Make me new in every way. Help me to walk in the newness You\'ve purchased for me. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-02', 'title': 'Love as Jesus Loved', 'scripture': 'John 13:34-35', 'body': 'A new command I give you: Love one another. As I have loved you, so you must love one another. By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you love one another.\n\nJesus set the standard for love—sacrificial, unconditional, and all-encompassing. This is our calling.', 'story': 'Marcus was known at his workplace as the guy who got things done—efficiently and alone. Then a colleague experienced a family crisis. Instead of offering shallow sympathy, Marcus showed up. He brought meals, he listened without judgment, he served without expecting recognition. Months later, his colleague asked, "Why did you do all that?" Marcus simply said, "Because Jesus did that for me." That question opened a door to one of Marcus\'s most meaningful ministry opportunities.', 'thoughts': 'Love isn\'t just a feeling; it\'s an action rooted in gratitude for how Jesus loved us. How can you show sacrificial love today—not to be seen, but because you\'ve been transformed by His love?', 'action': 'Identify someone you find difficult to love. Do one act of service for them today without telling anyone about it. Let Jesus\' love flow through you.', 'confession': 'Father, forgive me for the times I\'ve loved only those who could love me back. Fill my heart with Your selfless love so I can love as You loved—completely, without reservation, all-encompassing. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-03', 'title': 'Faith That Moves Mountains', 'scripture': 'Matthew 21:22', 'body': 'Therefore I tell you, whatever you ask for in prayer, believe that you have received it, and it will be yours.\n\nFaith is not passive hoping; it is active belief that God will do what He promises. Ask boldly and believe.', 'story': 'A small church in rural Nigeria faced an impossible problem: their only water source had dried up. The entire community depended on that well. The pastor called the church together and said, "Let\'s not panic. Let\'s pray with faith." They prayed, they dug deeper, they searched. Two weeks later, they found water at a level deeper than anyone thought existed. But more importantly, the community witnessed a God who responds to faith. Dozens came to faith that year because of how God moved in that "impossible" situation.', 'thoughts': 'What "mountain" are you facing right now? The size of your faith matters more than the size of your problem. God specializes in the impossible.', 'action': 'Write down one major prayer request. Pray over it daily this week with confident faith, thanking God in advance for what He will do.', 'confession': 'Lord, I confess my small faith. I often doubt before I even ask. Give me bold faith that trusts You completely. I believe—help my unbelief. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-04', 'title': 'The Heart of Love', 'scripture': '1 Corinthians 13:4-7', 'body': 'Love is patient, love is kind. It does not envy, it does not boast, it is not proud. It does not dishonor others, it is not self-seeking, it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs. Love does not delight in evil but rejoices with the truth. It always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always perseveres.\n\nThis is the portrait of Christ\'s love. Let it transform how you love others.', 'story': 'Jennifer was the office manager—detail-oriented, punctual, and intolerant of mistakes. Her staff feared rather than respected her. Then a coworker\'s child got sick, and Jennifer discovered she herself had missed countless moments with her own children in pursuit of "perfection." She started reading 1 Corinthians 13 daily. Slowly, she transformed. She became patient when people made errors, kind in her corrections, protective of her team\'s well-being. Her workplace culture shifted entirely. People started applying for positions just to work under her leadership.', 'thoughts': 'This passage isn\'t just poetic—it\'s the character of God manifested in flesh. Ask yourself: In which of these nine traits am I weakest? How can I grow in that specific area?', 'action': 'Pick the one trait from the passage where you struggle most (patience, kindness, honesty, etc.). Commit to actively practicing it in every interaction today.', 'confession': 'Jesus, You embodied every aspect of perfect love. I fall so short. Give me a loving heart that reflects Yours. Help me to be patient when I\'m frustrated, kind when I\'m annoyed, generous when I\'m scared. Transform me. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-05', 'title': 'Trust and Obey', 'scripture': 'Proverbs 3:5-6', 'body': 'Trust in the LORD with all your heart and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways submit to him, and he will make your paths straight.\n\nFaith means trusting God even when you cannot see the full picture. He promises to direct your path.', 'story': 'David had a five-year plan: college, career, marriage, house. It was solid. Then God asked him to leave his job and start a ministry no one thought would work. Every logical fiber in David\'s being resisted. But he chose to trust God\'s leading over his own understanding. Twenty years later, that ministry had transformed thousands of lives, including his own. Looking back, David said, "I\'m so glad God ignored my plan and showed me His."', 'thoughts': 'Trust isn\'t blind—it\'s based on God\'s character. He has never failed anyone who truly trusted Him. What are you trying to figure out through your own understanding when God is asking for trust?', 'action': 'Identify one area where you\'re leaning on your own understanding instead of trusting God. Write down what it would look like to fully trust Him in that situation.', 'confession': 'Father, forgive me for my stubborn independence. I keep trying to navigate my own path when You know the way perfectly. I choose to trust You over my limited understanding. Guide my steps. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-06', 'title': 'Known and Loved', 'scripture': 'Psalm 139:1-2', 'body': 'You have searched me, LORD, and you know me. You know when I sit and when I rise; you perceive my thoughts from afar.\n\nGod knows everything about you—and He loves you completely. You are never hidden from His sight or His care.', 'story': 'Emma felt invisible. In her large family, she was the quiet middle child. At school, she wasn\'t popular. Even her parents seemed to focus more on her siblings\' achievements. Then she discovered Psalm 139. As she read about God\'s intimate knowledge of her—her sitting down and rising up, her thoughts before she speaks them—something shifted. She realized that while the world might not see her, the Creator of the universe knew her completely and loved her deeply. That knowledge changed everything. She stopped seeking validation from people and found security in being known by God.', 'thoughts': 'You don\'t have to perform, achieve, or be noticed to be worthy of love. God sees you completely—your struggles, your potential, your pain, your joy—and He loves you as you are.', 'action': 'Take 10 minutes today to sit quietly and meditate on the fact that God knows you completely. Thank Him for seeing you.', 'confession': 'Thank You, Lord, for knowing me—truly knowing me. Not my public persona or my achievements, but the real me. Thank You for loving me anyway, completely. Help me find my worth in Your love, not in others\' approval. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-07', 'title': 'The Gift of Salvation', 'scripture': 'Romans 6:23', 'body': 'For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord.\n\nWhat we could never earn, God freely gives through Christ. This is grace—unmerited love and favor.', 'story': 'For years, Thomas worked to earn God\'s approval. He read the Bible more than anyone in his church, served tirelessly, tithed generously. But he lived in constant fear that he wasn\'t doing enough. Then he encountered the truth: salvation wasn\'t a wage he had to earn through works—it was a gift. The moment he truly grasped this, a burden lifted. He could serve from joy, not from fear. He could rest in what Christ had accomplished, not in his own striving.', 'thoughts': 'If salvation were based on what you deserved, what would you get? None of us can earn it. That\'s why it\'s called grace. Receive it as a gift today.', 'action': 'Write a thank-you note to Jesus expressing gratitude for the gift of salvation. Don\'t send it—just let your heart overflow with gratitude.', 'confession': 'Jesus, I cannot earn what You\'ve freely given. Forgive me for the times I\'ve tried to work my way into Your favor. I receive Your grace as the precious gift it is. Thank You. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-08', 'title': 'Love Covers All', 'scripture': '1 Peter 4:8', 'body': 'Above all, love each other deeply, because love covers a multitude of sins.\n\nWhen we love as Christ loved, we choose to overlook offenses, forgive freely, and restore relationships.', 'story': 'Rachel\'s sister had hurt her deeply years ago. They lived in a state of cold civility—polite but distant. Then their mother got sick. Suddenly, the old wound seemed insignificant compared to what really mattered. Rachel chose to love—not to pretend the hurt never happened, but to let love be bigger than the hurt. Over weeks of caring for their mother together, the sisters\' relationship healed. What love covered wasn\'t forgotten; it was forgiven and transformed into something better.', 'thoughts': 'Love doesn\'t mean pretending wrongs didn\'t happen. It means choosing to let them go, to restore, to give people grace the way Jesus has given you grace.', 'action': 'Is there someone you need to forgive? Reach out to them today with intention to restore the relationship, not to reopen the wound.', 'confession': 'Lord, my tendency is to keep score, to hold grudges, to make others pay for their mistakes. But You didn\'t do that to me. Give me a loving heart that forgives as I\'ve been forgiven. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-09', 'title': 'Faith Over Fear', 'scripture': '2 Timothy 1:7', 'body': 'For God has not given us a spirit of fear, but of power and of love and of a sound mind.\n\nWhatever frightens you, remember that God\'s love conquers all fear. Stand firm in faith.', 'story': 'Michael was terrified of public speaking. When his manager asked him to present to the entire company, panic set in. But he chose to remember: God gave him a spirit of power, not fear. He prayed, he prepared, and most importantly, he chose to trust God\'s empowering presence. His presentation wasn\'t perfect, but it was real. More importantly, he discovered that the fear had no power when he relied on God\'s strength instead of his own.', 'thoughts': 'Fear is real, but it\'s not bigger than God. Whatever you\'re afraid of, God is already there, already has a plan, and asks you to trust Him.', 'action': 'Name one fear that\'s holding you back. Pray specifically about it. Ask God for the spirit of power, love, and sound mind to overcome it.', 'confession': 'Father, I give You my fears. I confess that I\'ve been listening to the voice of fear instead of the voice of faith. Replace my fear with Your power, Your love, and Your peace. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

  {'date': '2026-01-10', 'title': 'The Ultimate Sacrifice', 'scripture': 'John 3:16', 'body': 'For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only Son, that whoever believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life.\n\nChrist\'s death proves the depth of God\'s love for us. This is the Gospel—the good news that changes everything.', 'story': 'When Joel\'s teenage daughter was diagnosed with a terminal illness, he was devastated. A pastor visited and asked, "Do you know that God the Father watched His own Son die?" For the first time, Joel understood: God wasn\'t distant from suffering. He had entered it. He had let His own Son experience it. That didn\'t take away the pain, but it gave meaning to the pain. God wasn\'t asking Joel to suffer alone—He had suffered too, out of love.', 'thoughts': 'John 3:16 isn\'t just about getting to heaven. It\'s about God\'s infinite love demonstrated in the ultimate sacrifice. That love is available to you today.', 'action': 'Meditate on the enormity of God\'s sacrifice. What does it cost you to truly believe in Jesus? What might it cost you if you don\'t?', 'confession': 'Jesus, thank You for dying for me. Thank You for paying the price for my sin, my shame, my brokenness. I receive Your sacrifice with humility and gratitude. Let Your love transform my life. Amen.', 'author': 'New Life Community Church'},

